# =============================================================================
# FLEET ACCIDENT REPORTER — ONBOARDING GUIDE
# =============================================================================
#
# This repo uses per-service .env files:
#
#   backend/.env         ← Server, database, AI, cloud storage (Node.js/Express)
#   web/.env             ← Frontend variables exposed to the browser (Vite)
#   mobile/.env          ← React Native / Expo variables (if applicable)
#
# QUICK START FOR NEW DEVELOPERS:
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Step 1  Copy the example files:
#            cp backend/.env.example  backend/.env
#            cp web/.env.example      web/.env
#
#  Step 2  Generate secure secrets (run once, save in your password manager):
#            node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('hex'))"
#          You need three unique values:
#            • JWT_SECRET         (backend/.env)
#            • SESSION_SECRET     (backend/.env)
#            • ENCRYPTION_KEY     (backend/.env)
#
#  Step 3  Choose and configure your DATABASE provider (default: Supabase):
#            → https://supabase.com/dashboard
#            Fill in DATABASE_URL, SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, etc.
#
#  Step 4  Set up Auth0:
#            → https://manage.auth0.com → Create Application (Regular Web App)
#            → Create a second Application (Single Page App) for the frontend
#            Fill in AUTH0_DOMAIN, AUTH0_CLIENT_ID, AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET, AUTH0_AUDIENCE
#
#  Step 5  Choose your CLOUD STORAGE provider (default: AWS S3):
#            AWS  → https://console.aws.amazon.com → IAM → Security credentials
#            Azure → https://portal.azure.com → Storage Accounts
#            GCP  → https://console.cloud.google.com → IAM → Service Accounts
#
#  Step 6  Choose your AI provider (default: OpenAI):
#            OpenAI     → https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#            Anthropic  → https://console.anthropic.com/keys
#            Mistral    → https://console.mistral.ai/api-keys
#            OpenRouter → https://openrouter.ai/keys  (access 100+ models)
#            Ollama     → docker run -d -p 11434:11434 ollama/ollama  (free, local)
#            Rekognition→ re-uses AWS credentials, no extra key needed
#
#  Step 7  Start the stack:
#            cd backend && npm install && npm run dev
#            cd web     && npm install && npm run dev
#
# SUPPORTED PROVIDERS AT A GLANCE:
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Database:      supabase | neon | postgresql | snowflake
#  Auth:          auth0 (OAuth2/OIDC) + JWT
#  Cloud Storage: aws (S3) | azure (Blob) | gcp (Cloud Storage)
#  AI / Vision:   openai | anthropic | aws_rekognition | ollama | mistral | openrouter
#  Email:         smtp | sendgrid | ses | resend | azure_email
# =============================================================================
